            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The fixes the problem:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/tui/tui.c b/src/nvim/tui/tui.c\nindex 1cdcf59fec..281322e383 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/tui/tui.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/tui/tui.c\n@@ -311,8 +311,7 @@ void tui_set_key_encoding(TUIData *tui)\n   case kKeyEncodingKitty:\n     // Progressive enhancement flags:\n     //   0b01   (1) Disambiguate escape codes\n-    //   0b10   (2) Report event types\n-    out(tui, S_LEN(\"\\x1b[>3u\"));\n+    out(tui, S_LEN(\"\\x1b[>1u\"));\n     break;\n   case kKeyEncodingXterm:\n     out(tui, S_LEN(\"\\x1b[>4;2m\"));\n```\nThis is strange. It seems that Xterm.js behaves as if \"Report event types\" implicitly enables \"Report all keys as escape codes\", so this may be an Xterm.js bug.\n\nRef https://github.com/xtermjs/xterm.js/pull/5600/changes (I haven't looked at it closely yet):\n```typescript\n  // Determine if we should use CSI u encoding\n  let useCsiU = false;\n\n  if (flags & KittyKeyboardFlags.REPORT_ALL_KEYS_AS_ESCAPE_CODES) {\n    useCsiU = true;\n  } else if (reportEventTypes) {\n    useCsiU = true;\n  } else if (flags & KittyKeyboardFlags.DISAMBIGUATE_ESCAPE_CODES) {\n    // Modifier-only keys already handled above\n    // Use CSI u for keys that would be ambiguous in legacy encoding\n    if (keyCode === 27 || keyCode === 127 || keyCode === 13 || keyCode === 9 || keyCode === 32) {\n      // Escape, Backspace, Enter, Tab, Space\n      useCsiU = true;\n    } else if (isFunc) {\n      useCsiU = true;\n    } else if (modifiers > 0) {\n      // Any modified key\n      useCsiU = true;\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (useCsiU) {\n    result.key = buildCsiUSequence(ev, keyCode, modifiers, eventType, flags, isFunc, isMod);\n    result.cancel = true;\n  } else {\n    // Legacy-compatible encoding for text keys without modifiers\n    if (ev.key.length === 1 && !ev.ctrlKey && !ev.altKey && !ev.metaKey) {\n      result.key = ev.key;\n    }\n  }\n```\nBoth `flags & KittyKeyboardFlags.REPORT_ALL_KEYS_AS_ESCAPE_CODES` and `reportEventTypes` set `useCsiU` unconditionally.",
