        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The buggy set of shift modifier doesn't automatically display anything after `<c-v>`, but I've played around with it til it displayed something. hope it's of some use. \n\n### Needs 3 key presses after <c-v> to display\n\n```\n<S-o> -> <c-v>, shift + 1, shift + 1, shift + 1\n<S-Þ> -> same as above but with 2\n<S-ÿ> -> same as above but with 3\n<S-ÿ> -> same as above but with 4\n<S-ÿ> -> same as above but with 5\n<S-ÿ> -> same as above but with 6\n<S-ÿ> -> same as above but with 7\n<S-ÿ> -> same as above but with 8\n<S-ÿ> -> same as above but with 9\n<S-NL> -> same as above but with 0\n```\n\n### Needs 1 more extra keypress after <c-v> + shift + <num> to display\n\n```\n^Aa -> <c-v>, shift + 1, a\n^Ab -> <c-v>, shift + 1, b\n^Ac -> <c-v>, shift + 1, c\n^Bi -> <c-v>, shift + 2, i\n^Cc -> <c-v>, shift + 3, c\n^Da -> <c-v>, shift + 4, a\n^Eo -> <c-v>, shift + 5, o\n^Fa -> <c-v>, shift + 6, a\n^Gh -> <c-v>, shift + 7, h\n^Hl -> <c-v>, shift + 8, l\n        b -> <c-v>, shift + 9, b\n^@i -> <c-v>, shift + 0, i\n```\n\n### some other shift modifier key that *works fine*\n```\n<S-~> -> <c-v>, shift + `\n<S-_> -> <c-v>, shift + -\n<S-+> -> <c-v>, shift + =\n<S-}> -> <c-v>, shift + ]\n```",
